The paper discusses the use of freeware routines to organize downloads from the Web-of-Science into a relational database and export matrices for further analysis. This involves techniques commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR), social networks (cs.SI), digital libraries (cs.DL), databases (cs.DB), and scientific data analysis (cs.SD). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
